<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="358">Etymology Named after the myrmecologist and collector of the type series James Trager.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="358">
diagnosis A member of a complex of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24885" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole Westwood" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole Westwood" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pheidole</taxonomicName>
species with giant majors having short bristly hair, in the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group and comprising 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181719" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole astur Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole astur Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astur">astur</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33914" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole oxyops Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole oxyops Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxyops">oxyops</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole praeusta Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole praeusta Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praeusta">praeusta</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181830" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole trageri Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole trageri Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trageri">trageri</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181830" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole trageri Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole trageri Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trageri">P. trageri</taxonomicName>
is distinguished among them by the following combination of traits. Major: lacking rugoreticulum on head; one carinula on each side of the dorsal cephalic midline reaches the occiput but otherwise nearly the entire posterior half of the dorsal surface of the head capsule is smooth and shiny; pronotum faintly bilobous in dorsaloblique view; propodeal spines stout, long, and vertical to the basal propodeal face; postpetiolar node seen from above trapezoidal; pronotum entirely smooth and shiny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="358">Minor: occiput narrowed somewhat, with nuchal collar; propodeal spine reduced to a denticle; entire mesosoma, including pronotum, foveolate and opaque.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="358">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 2.10, HL 2.44, SL 1.04, EL 0.26, PW 0.92. Paratype minor: HW 0.62, HL 0.80, SL 0.94, EL 0.16, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="358">color Major: light reddish yellow (light &quot;orange&quot;), color deepening from middle of head forward, reaching light reddish brown on mandibles.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="358">Minor: concolorous yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="358">Range Known only from the type series.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="358">Biology Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
